Colombia Stocks: Canacol Energy, Cementos Argos, Mineros SA

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-04-27T20:44:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/colombia-stocks-canacol-energy-cementos-argos-mineros-sa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.5 percent to 14,231.55, while the
Colcap Index fell 0.4 percent to 1,690.59, the most in a week.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNE)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in South America, rose for a second
day, rising 4.1 percent to 2,265 pesos, the highest in a week.
Investors are buying the stock on bets that a record 18 percent
plunge on April 25 was overdone, said  Rupert Stebbings , managing
director of international sales at Celfin Colombia SAS.  Cementos Argos (CEMARGOS CB), Colombia’s biggest cement
maker and sixth-largest concrete maker in the U.S., declined 0.4
percent to 10,620 pesos after U.S. Federal Reserve Chairman Ben S. Bernanke said the U.S. housing market remains “very weak.”  Mineros SA (MINEROS)  , Colombia’s largest gold-mining
company, jumped 0.2 percent to 6,450 pesos after saying it
increased production by 49 percent to 28,760 ounces in the first
quarter from a year ago, according to a regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
